From adfba73fce964122706f12f8ef6674263f68b04c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shayne Chen <shayne.chen@mediatek.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 18:59:45 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] mtk: mt76: mt7996: check if link BSS is initialized before
 dofing vif_link_remove

Problem:
Crash happens on switching an interface to MLD and then to legacy.

Root Cause:
A crash issue could occur with the following command sequence:

change_vif_links: old=0x0, new=0x1
change_vif_links: old=0x1, new=0x0

Since mvif->link[0] always points to vif->drv_priv, if the above command
sequence occurs, mt7996_vif_link_remove() will be called again without
a previous mt7996_vif_link_add().

Solution:
Add a check to ensure mlink->wcid is not NULL before proceeding with
vif link removal operations.

Feature:
Stability

Signed-off-by: Shayne Chen <shayne.chen@mediatek.com>
---
 mt7996/main.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/mt7996/main.c b/mt7996/main.c
index d6bd168af..8c0cbc541 100644
--- a/mt7996/main.c
+++ b/mt7996/main.c
@@ -472,6 +472,9 @@ void mt7996_vif_link_remove(struct mt76_phy *mphy, struct ieee80211_vif *vif,
 	};
 	int idx = msta_link->wcid.idx;
 
+	if (!mlink->wcid)
+		return;
+
 	cancel_delayed_work(&link->sta_chsw_work);
 
 	if (dev->recovery.hw_full_reset)
-- 
